  "summary": "Bitdefender Labs report (May 2023) by Victor Vrabie on RDStealer campaign (active from at least early 2022): targeted Tech/IT services company in East Asia. Threat actor deploys two custom Go tools: (1) File Collector (RDStealer) — monitors tsclient RDP shares, collects clipboard/keystrokes, steals KeePass/.rdp/SSH keys/MobaXterm/Xshell/mRemoteNG configs, archives to IDtimestamp.dat, notifies C2 at https://[local IP]:7443/pdr.php; (2) Logutil backdoor — Go DLL (logutil32/64.dll), XOR config, HTTPS C2 (/info, /update), QUIC proxy support, reflective DLL load, multi-platform. Persistence via SYSTEM32\\ncobjapi.dll DLL hijack (Winmgmt/DCOM); F-Secure side-loading; execution guardrails using hostname. C2 infra: 8 GCP IPs (all HK except 35.208.179.162 US); 40+ domains (ntp-update.com, 0g6666.com, sun-java.com, javaupdate-cdn.com); 3 TLS certs (op888kai.com, cugaa.com). Earlier-stage tools: AsyncRat + CobaltStrike Beacon (flash.javaupdate-cdn.com). Infrastructure active since at least 2020-03-29.",
